Package org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode.fy23.robot.old

Class RobotA

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.teamcode.fy23.robot.old.RobotA
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnyRobot
    public class RobotA
extends java.lang.Object
implements AnyRobot
    RobotA represents the competition robot. It contains five subsystems: a MecanumDrive, a FriendlyIMU, a PixelArm, a Claw, and a PlaneLauncher.

      • pidConsts

        public final PIDconsts pidConsts
        There's a few different preset things that this can get set to. The default is loaded from a file called "RobotA.pid" that gets saved by RobotAIMUDriveTuner, but you can also use a hard-coded value or disable PID entirely.

      • sdkMotorPidConsts

        public final PIDconsts sdkMotorPidConsts
        Default PID constants for the SDK's PID algorithm on individual DcMotorEx devices. Useful for RudimentaryRampToTarget, perhaps, which uses DcMotorEx.setVelocity() in the RUN_USING_ENCODER runmode.
